  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "`usePlugin` internally uses `require`, and `require` follows Node's resolution rules, including looking at `pkg.main`.\r\n\r\nWhen `pkg.main` is available, but the file it points to doesn't exist (e.g. it's wrong, or you forgot to compile) it throws a cryptic error complaining that the package doesn't exits, when it does.\r\n\r\nWe should detect this case and improve it.",
